text.tspan: Higher values indicate better human rights protection. The human rights scores measure protection from political
repression and violations of “physical integrity rights”.
Source: Human Rights Protection Scores – Christopher Farris (2014) and Keith Schnakenberg
Note: The protection scores are latent variable estimates and are described in more detail in the Sources Tab. The original dataset is published
with uncertainty estimates, which should be considered but cannot be shown here because of technical limitations.
